PY  - 2019
C3  - ICTRP jRCTs031190141
M3  - Trial registry record
AB  - INTERVENTION: nicotinamide riboside; NR 250 mg, pterostilbene 50 mg every day 2 capsules daily regardless of meals CONDITION: C16.320.925 / C18.452.284.960 Werner syndrome ; Werner syndrome PRIMARY OUTCOME: Safety at 26 and 52 weeks of the tested drugs in patients with Werner syndrome SECONDARY OUTCOME: ‐ Size of skin ulcer; ‐ NAD value; ‐ Inflammatory response; ‐ Blood test (lipid, blood glucose, liver function etc.); ‐ Handgrip strength test; ‐ Walking speed; ‐ Visceral fat; ‐ Skeletal muscle index by DEXA (Dual energy X ray absorption) method; ‐ Heel pad thickness; ‐ Evaluation of arteriosclerosis by blood flow dependent vasodilation test; ‐ CAVI (Cardio‐ankle vascular index); ‐ ABI (Ankle brachial pressure index); ‐ PWV (Pulse wave velocity); ‐ Insulin resistance by glucose clamp method; ‐ Glomerular filtration rate calculated with Cockroft‐Gault, MDRD, CKD‐EPI and cystatin C based methods; ‐ Urinary albumin excretion, urinary NAG, beta2‐microglobulin, L‐FABP, Kim‐1; ‐ Lipoprotein particle profile calculated by NMR or HPLC; ‐ Resting metabolic rate; ; ‐ Metabolomics; ‐ qPCR (Quantitative polymerase chain reaction); ‐ Western blotting; ‐ RNA sequence INCLUSION CRITERIA: Patients who meet all of the following criteria are included. 1) Patients who are diagnosed with Werner syndrome 2) Patients who explained the study contents using explanatory documents and obtained written consent for study participation from the person or the representative 3) Male or female 20 years old and more 4) Patients whose hematocrit value is judged to be clinically acceptable by the investigator or co‐investigator 5) Patients who can comply with the protocol requirements by the investigator or co‐investigator
